\details{
The function performs the following steps:
\enumerate{
\item Construct a Gaussian KDE and its first and second derivatives.
\item Calculate the signed curvature of the KDE.
\item Retain only the negative signed-curvature component and optionally apply
intensity weighting.
\item Smooth the weighted curvature using multiple Savitzky-Golay filters and
average the resulting profiles.
\item Detect strong local maxima from the averaged curvature profile as
shoulder-peak candidates.
\item Detect ordinary KDE peaks from derivative-based extrema.
\item Remove curvature candidates that are located near ordinary KDE peaks.
\item Remove weaker candidates located near stronger candidates.
